cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the empirical study of fake apps and their development, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). It also involves software engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses the development of fake apps and their ecosystem. The study involves collecting a large amount of data and analyzing it, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and data analysis (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the naming tendency and evasive strategies of fake developers, which can be categorized under social and information sciences (cs.SI).
